  <static seed="29" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionsCalculation/EquivalentFraction20.pg">
    <statement><p>Find an equivalent fraction to <m>\frac{1}{5}</m> with denominator <m>25</m>.</p>
<p><fillin characters="8" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{5}{25}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>From <m>1</m> to <m>5</m>, we multiplied by <m>5\div1=5</m>.</p>
<p>For a fraction, when we multiply the same number in both the numerator and denominator, the fraction<rsq/>s value doesn<rsq/>t change. We have:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ \frac{1}{5}=\frac{1\cdot5}{5\cdot5} = \frac{5}{25} }</m></p>
</solution>
